I am seeking communications from on or after January 1, 2019 until current day. The types of communications include emails and other messages between the CDC and Google or Alphabet employees; internal documents or reports detailing vaccine-related content on Google’s services; internal documents outlining any partnerships between the agency and Google or Alphabet on public interventions or location data; and minutes of meetings between Google and/or Alphabet employees or lawyers and officials from the CDC. This information is being sought on behalf of Bloomberg News and Bloomberg.com and Bloomberg Businessweek for dissemination to the general public. Through this request, I am gathering information on how the CDC worked with Google to track the spread of the coronavirus and other public health issues. This information is of current interest to the public because it would help explain what steps the CDC and these companies have taken to try and protect people, many of them U.S. citizens, to track and prevent serious public health and safety issues. I agree to pay reasonable duplication fees for the processing of this request. However, if it is possible to waive any fees, that would be welcome. Release of this information is in the public interest because it will contribute significantly to the public’s understanding of vaccine-related safety information, as well as hold large public companies accountable for protecting the hundreds of millions of people who use their services. Copies of all electronic correspondence between the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and the cruise company Carnival Corporation and PLC, as well as its subsidiaries Princess Cruises and Holland America Line, dated between January 26, 2020 and June 1, 2020. Please search the emails of CDC Director Robert R. Redfield, as well as the top five senior-most employees who report to Director Redfield, for correspondence with anyone with an email address ending in @carnival.com, @carnivalukgroup.com, @princess.com, @princesscruises.com, @princesstours.com, and @hollandamerica.com. Carnival Corporation's Princess Cruises and Holland America Line cruises have each been in the news following reports that passengers on their cruises were exposed to the coronavirus, also known as COVID-19 or the Wuhan Coronavirus. Princess Cruises first received formal verification that one of its customers was infected on the Diamond Princess ship around February 1, 2020. https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/22/world/asia/coronavirus-japan-cruise-ship.html A second ship called Westerdam from the Holland American Line was suspected to have been exposed to the virus, though it was later shown to be a false positive. https://time.com/5785109/coronavirus-confirmed-westerdam-cruise-ship/ On March 2, another one of Carnival Corporation's Princess Cruises ships, the Grand Princess, was linked to cases of the coronavirus. https://www.businessinsider.com/california-reports-first-coronavirus-death-sacramento-cruise-2020-3 The CDC became involved publicly on February 16 when the Department of State repatriated Americans who were on the Diamond Princess, including many who were exposed to the virus. https://www.businessinsider.com/how-diamond-princess-cruise-ship-coronavirus-quarantine-went-wrong-2020-2 For the purpose of assessing fees, please note that I am submitting this request in my capacity as a full-time journalist at Insider, Inc. in New York City. The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not. Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires. Sincerely, Becky Peterson {COVID-19} (D (Date Range for Record Search: From 1/26/2020 To 6/1/2020)
